7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Anyword and QuillBot share a solid foundation of core features including Short Form, Tone Control, Multilingual, Browser Extension. Where Anyword pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Long Form and Templates and Api Access and Team Collaboration, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, QuillBot uniquely offers Plagiarism Check, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Anyword holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while QuillBot scores 7/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, QuillBot comes in at a lower starting price of Free, while Anyword begins at $49/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Anyword's free tier and QuillBot's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
