b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Anyword is best suited for performance marketers, ad copy, email marketing, data driven teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. QuillBot, meanwhile, shines for paraphrasing, summarizing, academic writing, students, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2013, Anyword describes itself as \"Data-driven AI copywriting with predictive performance scores.\" QuillBot, established in 2017, positions itself as \"AI paraphrasing and summarization tool trusted by students.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Anyword** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (8 vs 5), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean QuillBot is a poor choice — far from it. QuillBot excels in its own right, particularly for paraphrasing and summarizing.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value predictive performance scoring is genuinely useful, go with Anyword. If best paraphrasing tool with multiple modes matters more to you, QuillBot is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
